name: Poultry recalled BrucePac meat recall
summary: Due to possible listeria contamination, BrucePac has recalled 10 million pounds of ready-to-eat meat and poultry products. The recall affects 75 different products distributed nationwide and sold at popular grocery stores and restaurants. The meat products include lunch meats, deli meats, meat salads, and poultry products. Consumers are urged to check the USDA website for a full list of the affected products and to discard any recalled items immediately. Listeria can cause serious infections, especially in pregnant women, the elderly, and those with weakened immune systems.

name: Addison's disease
summary: TikToker Taylor Rousseau Grigg, 25, died from Addison's disease, a rare chronic condition that affects the adrenal glands. Addison's disease occurs when the body does not produce enough of the hormone cortisol, which is essential for regulating blood pressure, blood sugar, and immune function. It can also cause symptoms such as fatigue, weight loss, and darkened skin. Grigg's family revealed her cause of death less than a week after she died. The news has raised awareness about the condition and its potential complications.
